
[1]hydragogue

   HY'DRAGOGUE, n. hy'dragog. [Gr. water, and a leading or drawing; to
   lead or drive.] A medicine that occasions a discharge of watery humors;
   a name that implies a supposition that every purgative has the quality
   of evacuating a particular humor. But in general, the stronger
   cathartics are hydragogues.
